name: Lexington-Fayette County Health Department
tweet: Remember, our harm reduction program has a Sharing Shelf to help those who need warm supplies for the upcoming months: • hats, gloves, socks or any winter clothing item • deodorant • toothpaste & toothbrushes • bath soap & body wash • wash cloths. 3/3

name: Lexington-Fayette County Health Department
tweet: We also had 8 people use on-site referrals to treatment for substance use disorder, bringing the total to 424. Our free, anonymous/confidential harm reduction services are offered 1-4pm Mon, 3-6:30pm Wed & 11am-4pm Fri.  2/3

name: Lexington-Fayette County Health Department
tweet: In November, we had 1,642 visits to our #needleexchange program, including 58 1st-time participants, as we fight the spread of #hepatitisC and #HIV!
